SubjectRegulations Repealing the Fish Health Protection Regulations
PrecisRegulations Repealing the FISH HEALTH PROTECTION REGULATIONS in order to (1) remove redundant regulations related to interprovincial movement of salmonids; (2) streamline regulatory requirements for industry, as the Canadian Food Inspection Agencyâ€™s Domestic Movement Control Program is now in place; and (3) complete the transfer of regulatory responsibility for the domestic movement of salmonids to the Canadian Food Inspection Agency.
